Known-answer test vectors vendored under */testdata/PQCsignKAT_*.rsp(.gz) are
the upstream NIST KAT files from the FAEST (faest-rs) and MAYO (MAYO-C)
projects (the FAEST sets regenerated with the upstream NIST harness by
tools/faest_kat_gen) and are redistributed under their original licenses
(MIT / Apache-2.0).

Known-answer test vectors vendored under mldsa/testdata/ are extracted from
the NIST ACVP-Server project (https://github.com/usnistgov/ACVP-Server,
ML-DSA-FIPS204 gen-val JSON files; the pinned commit is recorded in the
vector file's provenance field). As works of the U.S. Government, NIST
materials are not subject to copyright in the United States (see the
ACVP-Server license).

The MAYO and FAEST names and specifications belong to their respective teams.
ML-DSA is specified by NIST FIPS 204.
